item.title: GovBrief Today #384
item.description: The government made it impossible for refugees to get green cards, then ordered their arrest for not having them. DHS halted green card processing months ago for dozens of countries, and yesterday issued a memo authorizing federal agents to arrest and indefinitely detain any refugee who hasn't obtained one. An estimated 100,000 people entered this country legally, were vetted, and were promised protection. Now they're targets. No administration has ever done this. Meanwhile, judges in two states have documented more than 140 court order violations, and the government's own attorney called a ruling against them "lawless abuse." Today a judge in Minnesota issued the first contempt finding, with a DOJ attorney personally liable for $500 daily fines. Courts are reaching for personal consequences because the government treated judicial orders as suggestions. Call your senators and your representative and demand they reverse the green card freeze that made this manufactured crisis possible. We've emailed 6,200+ stories over 384 straight nights. item.title: N bombs within, warning. White person calls black ICE agent a "house Nword working for the KKK"
item.description:
Hadn't seen this on imgur yet. Black commentary, cultural permissiveness, and potentially offensive language and attitudes within. Lezzgo
Case study in question
A fantastic discourse on the perennial question of "can white people use the N word." This conversation may be disconcerting to some. To many people of color, it is a regular occurrence to know that wypipo (white people) still frequently use Nbombs at POC, permission or not.
This is NOT an exception or loophole to the socially accepted norms that white people are rightfully scrutinized and sanctioned for dropping Nbombs. It may be an override given very specific circumstances.
There is a sentiment in skinfolk (POC) communities that black conservatives aren't maga, they're just desperate for white acceptance. They listen to white people opinion more than black. So, maybe this WAS the right messenger after all. This isn't afternoon high tea, there will offenses given, and taken, in the commentary discourse. Go forth with curiosity, courtesy, and comedy. Can wypipo use the N word? Can THIS white person use the term "house Nword" for black ICE officers? These are the philosophical queries of our time
